Okay, time to push the pawn. But first, we've got to move that bishop further back.
You always have to really consider what you're doing to your kingside when you push another pawn to drive back the bishop. Will it hurt you if he sacrifices the bishop for the pawn (or two)? Have you opened yourself up too much?
